SIMPLE: internal
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Internal
<hw>In*tern"al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>internus</ets>; akin to <ets>interior</ets>. See
<er>Interior</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Inward; interior; being within any limit or surface;
inclosed; -- opposed to <ant>external</ant>; <as>as, the
<ex>internal</ex> parts of a body, or of the earth</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Derived from, or dependent on, the thing itself;
inherent; <as>as, the <ex>internal</ex> evidence of the divine origin of
the Scriptures</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Pertaining to its own affairs or interests;
especially, (said of a country) domestic, as opposed to
<ant>foreign</ant>; <as>as, <ex>internal</ex> trade; <ex>internal</ex>
troubles or war.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Pertaining to the inner being or the heart;
spiritual.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With our Savior, <qex>internal</qex> purity is everything.</q>
<rj><qau>Paley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Intrinsic; inherent; real.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>internal</qex> rectitude of our actions in the sight of
God.</q> <rj><qau>Rogers.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 779 --></p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Lying toward the mesial plane;
mesial.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Internal angle</b></col> <fld>(Geom.)</fld>, <cd>an
interior angle. See under <er>Interior</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Internal
gear</b></col> <fld>(Mach.)</fld>, <cd>a gear in which the teeth project
inward from the rim instead of outward.</cd></cs></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Inner; interior; inward; inland;
inside.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Internal-combustion engine</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Internal-combustion</ent>⟦br⟧
